While "scouting" my mobile application, Starling.contextValid came up as the top function in the allocations ranking. 

 /*\* Indicates if the Context3D object is currently valid (i.e. it hasn't been lost or
disposed). Beware that each call to this method causes a String allocation (due to
internal code Starling can't avoid), so do not call this method too often.
*/
public function get contextValid():Boolean {
   return mContext && mContext.driverInfo != "Disposed"
}

I don't quite understand the comment above. "Disposed" should be a static constant in the Starling class to avoid string creation & garbage collection. Event if the driverInfo getter has string allocations itself, at least we'll save one per call:

private static const DRIVER_DISPOSED:String = "Disposed";
public function get contextValid():Boolean {
   return mContext && mContext.driverInfo != DRIVER_DISPOSED
}

